      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THINKYAHOT (3) finds a nice race third up. He's placed in two runs back, battling well on the heavy ground at Sale last start when beaten half a length. First go synthetic now but should take plenty of beating. Wary of LIFT NET (9) who resumes for the McEvoy yard. He didn't fire in his debut at Pakenham but has been given a spell since then and can be much improved. Respecting. PEIRIANT (1) was just fair last time at Sale but had been good into third prior at Cranbourne and is open to further improvement. He's in the each-way mix. ALPHABET (4) struggled on the heavy second-up but had been good on resumption and onto drier should help.",
